{"title":"Cannondale Topstone Drops 160g Thanks to LAB71 Treatment","link":"https://bikerumor.com/cannondale-topstone-lab71-gravel-bike/","date":1680053273000,"content":"<p>If you want the best Cannondale has to offer, look no further than their new <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cannondale-lab-71-road-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">LAB71 collection</a>. Calling it their ‘best of the best’, this is where you’ll find the most technologically advanced Cannondale Models. Like the new LAB71 Topstone. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Offered only as a frameset, the top-end Topstone drops more than 160g thanks to an advanced carbon layup. The frame still includes the Kingpin suspension system which provides 30mm of suspension travel at the rear wheel. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_DreamBuild_0002-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_DreamBuild_0002-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Lab71 Topstone with bags from side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_DreamBuild_0002-Large.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_DreamBuild_0002-Large-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_DreamBuild_0002-Large-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_DreamBuild_0002-Large-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sold with a rigid Superlight Series 0 carbon fork, the LAB71 Topstone has plenty of accessory mounts including three-pack mounts on the fork legs and downtube, top tube mounts, two additional bottle mounts, and fender mounts. It’s also <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cannondale-smartsense-gives-all-new-2022-synapse-integrated-lights-radar-on-single-battery/\" target=\"_blank\">SmartSense compatible if you want to add lights and radar. </a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0006-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0006-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Lab71 Topstone top tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0006-Large.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0006-Large-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0006-Large-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0006-Large-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cannondale-evo-road-bike-lab71-15k/\" target=\"_blank\">LAB71 SuperSix EVO</a>, a big part of the draw is also a unique LAB71 finish with gloss Marble Oxblood on the back third of the bike, satin Jet Black finish on the rest, and Smoke Brushed Chrome accents. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_TopstoneFrameset_GeoTable-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"534\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_TopstoneFrameset_GeoTable-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Lab71 Topstone geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_TopstoneFrameset_GeoTable-Large.jpeg 534w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_TopstoneFrameset_GeoTable-Large-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_TopstoneFrameset_GeoTable-Large-80x120.jpeg 80w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Available in five sizes, each rolls on 700c wheels with tire clearance of 700c x 45mm. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0007-Large.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0007-Large.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Lab71 Topstone frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0007-Large.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0007-Large-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0007-Large-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/C23_LAB71_Topstone_Frameset_Beauty_0007-Large-768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sold as a frameset for $4,500, that price includes the frame, fork, a SAVE Carbon SmartSense seat post, a StrapRack Tool/Stuff carrier, and front and rear thru axles. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.cannondale.com/en-us/bikes/road/gravel/topstone-carbon/topstone-lab71-frameset\" target=\"_blank\">cannondale.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cannondale-topstone-lab71-gravel-bike/\">Cannondale Topstone Drops 160g Thanks to LAB71 Treatment</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"dfb404e6963446e80a6fc1e92803a8c5adfc966c8b770abb4dc60e10923b0a4d","category":"Cycling"}